  7  /-!

  9  # Natural number multiplicity
 10  
 11  This file contains lemmas about the multiplicity function (the maximum prime power divding a number).
 12  
 13  # Main results
 14  
 15  There are natural number versions of some basic lemmas about multiplicity.
 16  
 17  There are also lemmas about the multiplicity of primes in factorials and in binomial coefficients.
 18  -/

 24  /-- The multiplicity of a divisor `m` of `n`, is the cardinality of the set of
 25    positive natural numbers `i` such that `p ^ i` divides `n`. The set is expressed
 26    by filtering `Ico 1 b` where `b` is any bound at least `n` -/

 77  /-- The multiplicity of a prime in `fact n` is the sum of the quotients `n / p ^ i`.
 78    This sum is expressed over the set `Ico 1 b` where `b` is any bound at least `n` -/
